The upper sage hears the Dao and finds it profound and good,
Diligent in following it, for their nature is near;
The middle sage hears the Dao and doubts it shallowly,
As if it exists or does not, for their nature is distant;
The lower sage hears the Dao and finds it unnatural,
Laughing at it, for their nature is opposed—
Not to laugh is insufficient for the Dao;
The Dao’s symbols must be displayed.»

gzi said:
*The **Dao/Way** of Heaven and Earth*
*Begins and yet has an end,*
*Ends and yet returns to beginning.*

When yang-qi rests as the hidden dragon,
It can melt metal;
When yin-qi is at ease with frost,
It can freeze ice;
When wood thrives in the autumn hair’s breadth,
It can grow to a hundred fathoms;
When water delights in the trickling stream,
It can become the sea;
When birds take joy in the egg’s warmth,
They can soar high;
When beasts prepare in the womb’s embrace,
They can run far.

